⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Alex
node ACO · ACO · ⟦Alex:ACO:f91bf4⟧

WHO   — Alex — the droog who loved Beethoven
WHAT  — The vile protagonist whose free will is the book's subject: conditioned out of violence (and music), then restored, then choosing on his own to change.
WHERE — ACO · A CLOCKWORK ORANGE  Framework inputs: A Clockwork Orange (Anthony Burgess, 1962)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the question only bites if the man whose choice is removed is genuinely guilty — Alex is no innocent.
HOW   — By ultra-violence and theft, then the Ludovico nausea, then, in the final chapter, a freely-chosen weariness with cruelty.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I did real evil and chose it — then they cut the choosing out of me and called it a cure; but a man who cannot pick the wrong is no man, only a clockwork.

